<br>
And Lor, who determines what a camp is?  By your mentality, D! should be segrated into 3 camps or 4, since what the majority of people consider the D1 camp consists of more than one room.  So, it would be Frenzied, Little room with 3 frogs on the side, Stage, and either the top hallway or the back hallway.  Same with D2.  That's be about 5 or 6 camps.<br>
<br>
A camp, in my view, and many others is basically a certain area that can be held by one group.  The D1 / D2 seperations were made when Sebilis was discovered at level 50's, ergo it was very diffcult to hold such a large area.  As people's characters grew, so did the lines of said camps.  <br>
<br>
As for the 40+ people in zone.....if I log on and go to Velks and find that there is more than 25 people in zone, I leave.  The zone can't handle much more and getting one spider per half hour is a pointless waste of time.  Same with Sebilis or any other zone.  Each zone can handle a certain amount of players before being congested.<br>
<br>
Rewritting history won't get the vile taste out of my mouth.  A group demanded to take over part of our camp, meanwhile there were several other choice spots available, such as King's, Illis Jail, NG was even opened at the time.  No effort was made by said group to go somewhere else.  It was a &quot;stomp my feet I want D2 and I'm gonna turn blue until I get my way&quot;.<br>
<br>
As for sharing, I certainly shared.  The group demanded D2, barged in and went into the room at the back with the stage (d2 by your own choice of words).  I didn't touch one single wee frog in that room, since you wanted it so badly.  Don't complain and dare to lecture me when you got EXACTLY what was demanded and threatened.  <br>
<br>
Gee, I treated your group with the exact same amount of respect you gave mine, actually ...with more :P~  Which was the point of this post - to survive among the twits we all begin to act like the twits (Gag!)<br>
<br>
If any of the tells, shouts and /ooc would have had a semblance of politeness and courtesy, as opposed to demands and threats, allowing your group to move to a spot we were camping would have been no problems.  But your group chose to be arrogant, nasty, pig headed and insulting.  Gee, what a surprise that you didn't get welcomed with open arms.<br>
<br>
